Source: elock
Section: gui
Maintainer: Alexander Kerner <lunohod@openinkpot.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), autoconf, automake, pkg-config, libecore-dev, libevas-dev, libedje-dev, libkeys-dev
XCS-Cross-Host-Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), autoconf, automake, pkg-config
XCS-Cross-Build-Depends: libecore-dev, libevas-dev, libedje-dev, libkeys-dev
Priority: optional
Standards-Version: 3.8.3

Package: elock
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: simple EFL-based screen locker for OpenInkpot
 elock is a screen locker for OpenInkpot with two operation modes:
  - hardware-assisted. Key locking is performed by hardware, elock just displays
    the "device locked" screen.
  - software-based. elock works like a usual screensaver program

Package: elock-dbg
Architecture: any
Depends: elock (= ${binary:Version})
Description: simple EFL-based screen locker for OpenInkpot -- debugging information
 elock is a screen locker for OpenInkpot with two operation modes:
  - hardware-assisted. Key locking is performed by hardware, elock just displays
    the "device locked" screen.
  - software-based. elock works like a usual screensaver program
 .
 This package contains debugging information for elock.
